solution: ```class Solution {
    public int shipWithinDays(int[] weights, int days) {
        int left = 0, right = 0;
        for (int w : weights) {
            left = Math.max(left, w);
            right += w;
        }
        while (left < right) {
            int mid = left + (right - left) / 2;
            int need = 1, cur = 0;
            for (int w : weights) {
                if (cur + w > mid) {
                    need++;
                    cur = 0;
                }
                cur += w;
            }
            if (need <= days) right = mid;
            else left = mid + 1;
        }
        return left;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n log S) where S is the sum of weights
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Binary search on the capacity range [max weight, total weight]. For each candidate capacity, a greedy scan counts required days. The search converges on the minimal feasible capacity.

